!1| --------------------------------------------------
!1| Static websites
!1| --------------------------------------------------

!2| --------------------------------------------------
!2| github.com
!2| --------------------------------------------------

1. Create a public repository
2. Upload a file called "index.html".
3. Open repository settings and go to "GitHub Pages".
4. Choose a source (that is, choose a branch that contains the files) for your website.
5. Wait a few seconds.
6. It should be published!
